prefix.translation[0].definitions[0].def: a group of letters that is added to the beginning of a word to change its meaning and make a new word, such as ‘un’ in ‘untie’ or ‘mis’ in ‘misunderstand’
prefix.translation[0].definitions[1].def: a number or letter that comes before other numbers or letters, especially a group of numbers that comes before a telephone number when you are calling someone in a different area
prefix.translation[0].definitions[2].def: a title such as ‘Ms’ or ‘Dr’ used before someone’s name
prefix.translation[1].definitions[0].def: to add a prefix to a word, name, or set of numbers
prefix.translation[1].definitions[1].def: to say something before the main part of what you have to say
